definitions.definition: The Chinese foot , a traditional Chinese unit of length based on the human forearm .
( Mainland China ) The Chinese unit of length standardized in 1984 as / 3 of a meter .
( Taiwan ) The Taiwanese unit of length standardized as / 33 of a meter , identical to the Japanese shaku .
( Hong Kong ) The chek or Hong Kong foot , a unit of length standardized as 0.371475 meters .
